---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="My Summer of Cricket" description="My Summer of Cricket, Nikhil Kulkarni's debut book weaving together cricket, migration, identity, and belonging.">

  <div class="page-header">
    <p class="page-label">Writing</p>
    <h1>My Summer of Cricket</h1>
    <p class="intro">A debut book that follows a landmark cricket summer across Australia, exploring what it means to be a fan, a migrant, and a father raising daughters in a new country.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="content">

    <div class="book-hero">
      <div class="book-cover">
        <img src="/images/book-cover.png" alt="My Summer of Cricket book cover" />
      </div>
      <div class="book-summary">
        <h2>About the book</h2>
        <p><em>My Summer of Cricket</em> is memoir and sports writing woven together. It follows a landmark Border–Gavaskar Trophy summer in which I travelled across Australia to watch the cricket, using those journeys as a lens to explore what it means to be a cricket tragic, an Indian-Australian, and a dad raising two daughters who might never feel the same pull toward the game that I do.</p>
        <p>The book moves between stadium terraces and late-night radio, between childhood memories of cricket in India and the strange, warm experience of falling in love with Australian cricket from the outside in.</p>
        <p>At its core, it's about belonging, and about the unlikely ways sport can help you find it.</p>
        <a href="https://mysummerofcricket.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cta-btn">Visit the book site →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Themes</h2>
      <div class="themes-grid">
        <div class="theme">
          <h3>Cricket as cultural bridge</h3>
          <p>Between India and Australia, between generations, between the game as it was and as it's becoming.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="theme">
          <h3>Migration &amp; identity</h3>
          <p>What it means to rebuild a life in a new country, and to find your place through unexpected things like Test cricket.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="theme">
          <h3>Fatherhood</h3>
          <p>Raising daughters in Australia and wrestling with the question of how sport, love, and legacy get passed on.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="theme">
          <h3>The cricket tragic</h3>
          <p>The joy, obsession, humour, and community of following a sport that takes five days and still doesn't always produce a result.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
